inn1.comm: pitches on leg and middle stump. Jaques goes back and defends it off his hips to midwicket
hit on the pads and the ball goes to point. Watson takes off from the non-strikers end but Jaques isn't interested. Watson makes it back in time.
defended to square leg
strays down leg side, clips the pad on the way through to Dhoni
and Jaques and Australia are away, forced wide of mid-on for two
wide outside off stump and Jaques slices it wide of Yuvraj at point for one
defended on the off side.
pitches on off stump and moves away from Jaques prods tentatively and gets beaten
pitches on off stump and angles away from Jaques with the arm, Jaques pushes foward and gets beaten
defended back to  the bowler
strays down leg side, clips the pad and goes to square leg for a leg bye
short of a length outside off stump, Wastson goes back and tries to cut but doesn't make contact
pitches on Jaques leg stump and drifts down leg side, wide called
pitches outside off stump and nips in a touch, Jaques plays inside the line and gets beaten
short of a length and Jaques charges down and tries to heave it down the ground, the ball takes a thick edge and flies over Yuvraj at point
glanced down to fine leg for one
full on middle stump, Watson gets forward and pushes past midwicket for one
outside off stump, Jaques swishes at it but misses
defended back to the bowler
pitches outside off stump and moves away off the pitch, Watson lets it go
short of a length outside off stump, Watson gets forward and punches through cover-point
short of a length outside off stump and moves away from the right-hander, Watson plays back but gets beaten
played down to fine leg for one
that one bounced a little more, Jaques runs it down to third man for one
short ball and Watson tries to pull but doesn't time it well enough to find the boundary he was looking for
pitches outside off stump and moves away, Watson is drawn into the drive and gets beaten, that was close to being wide
much straighter this time, driven back to Agarkar
short of a length outside off stump, punched off the back foot to cover
full on off and middle stump, Watson tries to hit through the line but gets a thick inside edge past square leg for two
too full this time and Watson thumps it to cover where Raina does well to cut it off
short of a length on off stump, Watson gets a thick edge down to third man for one
good length on off stump and shapes into Watson a touch, driven back to the bowler
tries to drive down the ground but another thick outside edge goes to point
Munaf drops in a touch short and Watson rocks back to pull, he doesn't connect as well as he'd have liked and the ball just manages to beat Sehwag at midwicket
thick edge flies down to third man for one
that cut back into Jaques who gets an inside edge past the stumps on the leg side for one
defended on the leg side
drifting on to the pads and Jaques comfortably eases it past midwicket for one
dropped! Watson tries to force it on the leg side and the edge lobs in the direction of mid=off. Harbhajan runs across and dives to his left, he gets both hands to it but grasses it
smashed over deep cover for four
lofted over wide long-on and that just clears the fence, Jaques dragged that from outside off stump
dabbed on the leg side for one
driven to mid on for one
on off stump, Watson tries to drive but the ball nips back and goes between bat and body
driven to cover
on off stump, that also cut back into Watson who defends it on the leg side
full and in the slot, Watson lofts it straight over Munaf's head and down to the boundary. Australia are getting a move on
whack! Just a touch short of a length and Watson hammers it to the wide long-on fence
forced past midwicket and Australia have got their run-rate over six an over
slapped through midwicket for another boundary
full on the pads, flick to deep midwicket
steps down the track and lofts it over cover, the ball bounces twice and goes over the fence
run down to third man for one
driven to mid-off
defended back to the bowler
cut to point
driven on the up on the front foot past cover for four
India have the breakthrough, on off stump, Jaques steps forward and tries to loft it over the off side, the ball stops on him and flies off the edge, Sehwag at mid-off takes a simple catch
defended back to the bowler
dabbed on the off side and the batsmen set off for a quick single. Very slack on India's part to let that run go
drifts on to leg stump, Watson should have done better than hit it straight to square leg
on off stump, that kept lower that usual, dabbed on the off side for another single
worked down to fine leg for one
Ponting gets forward and is hit on the pad outside off stump, the Indians go up in half-hearted appeal
driven to mid-off
Ponting gets forward and lofts on the up over mid-off for four
left alone by the batsman
pitches outside off stump and cuts back into the right-hander, chopped down to third man for one
loose ball first up, short and wide outside off stump and Ponting latches on to it and creams it past point for four more
short and wide outside off stump again but this time Ponting doesn't time it well and can't beat the point fielder
left alone outside off stump, that was much closer to off stump than the previous two
pitches outside off stump and moves away, the batsman lets it go
full and wide outside off stump, Ponting gets forward and drives past mid-off for four
driven on the off side
drifts down leg side and Pathan starts with a wide
pitches on off stump and cuts back into Watson who gets hit high on the thigh, muted appeal for leg before
defended back to the bowler
drifting on to the pads again, flicked past square leg for one
full outside off stump, it doesn't swing back into Ponting who drives it to cover
shorter in length and that one moves back into Ponting who tries to guide it to third man but the ball hits pad then bat and goes to point
driven to mid-on
outside off stump and just short of a length, driven to mid-on
that was straight on the stumps, Watson backed away outside leg stump, made room, and thumped it down the ground for four, excellent improvisation!
driven to mid-on, along the ground this time
pitches just outside leg stump, played to midwicket
played down to third man for one
leg-stump line again, the ball clips the thigh pad for a leg bye
half-volley outside off stump and Ponting gets forward and drives it past mid-off for four
caught at short fine leg! That was a touch short and Ponting rocked back and tried to pull, he didn't connect well and hit it straight to Tendulkar at short fine leg
defended back to the bowler
wide outside off stump and Martyn tries to play at it but doesn't connect
another gimme outside off stump, Martyn dispatches the half-volley to the cover fence to get off the mark
full again but closer to off stump, driven to cover
short of a length and angling across the right-hander, played down to third man
straighter line on off stump, defended on the off side
shorter in length and a touch quicker as well, Martyn tries to get on top of it and cut but gets beaten
defended off the back foot to point
beaten! That pitch on middle and off and moved just enough to beat the batsman's tentative prod
short and outside off stump, Martyn steps down, backs away and throws everything at it but fails to make contact
Watson begins with a four after the break, whipped off his pads through midwicket
left alone outside off stump
fifty for Watson, not the ideal way to bring it up but well played! He gets a thick inside edge past the wicketkeeper for four to fine leg
full again, on the pads and Watson forces it through square leg for four more
dropped short and Watson goes back, swivels and pulls through midwicket for the fourth four in the over

caught! But that so nearly went down, Martyn edges it as though he was giving slip practice and Dravid fumbles the easiest of chances not once but twice. Howvere, Dhoni was alert enough to pouch it off the rebound
left alone outside off stump
pitches on leg stump and hits Clarke high on the thigh
pitches outside off stump and moves away from Clarke who gets forward and lets it go
short of a length oustide off stump and Clarke plays it straight to point
excellent line and length in the channel outside off stump, Clarke lets it go and RP Singh finishes a wicket maiden
slower ball on off stump, defended to point
Pathan slips in the slower ball, Watson waits for it and lofts it right back over the bowler for four
strays down leg side, wide called
outside off stump, guided down to third man
much straighter in line, defended on the leg side
played back to the bowler on the front foot
pushed to midwicket
room offered outside off stump, played to third man for one
shorter in length and on middle stump, defended back to the bowler
wider outside off stump, left alone by the batsman
tight line on off stump, defended on the off side
played to point, the batsmen decide against the single, Yuvraj fires in the return
defended towards cover, just the one run off the over
defended back to the bowler
slips down leg side, wide called
outside off stump but the batsman gets across on one knee and plays it down to fine leg
played past midwicket for one
pushed down the ground towards long-on for one
short and wide outside off stump, Clarke will be disappointed that he cut that straight to point
short and wide outside off again, this time he gets a single to deep point
short of a length and on the pads, Clarke flicks it forward of square for four
defended on the leg side
short and wide outside off stump, Clarke cuts hard and beats point and the ball reaches the fence
closer to off stump on this occasion, left alone
much better line, pitching on middle and off and moving away from the right-hander from over the wicket, Clarke lets it go
moves away from Clarke again, left alone
flat trajectory on middle stump, played to midwicket
tossed up a touch, Watson gets forward and plays it to midwicket
shorter in length, Watson forces it down the ground on the back foot for one
turned to square leg
played to square leg again on the front foot
just outside off stump and shorter in length, Clarke waits for it and nudges it to short third man
on leg stump, pushed into the vacant midwicket region for one
full and wide outside off stump, Clarke smashes it past mid-off for four
shorter in length, dabbed in front of point for one
bouncer, Watson tries to create room by backing away and swerves out of the way
defended on the off side
short again and Watson backs away yet again, this time he pulls it ferociously over midwicket for six
four down to third man, that was the straighter ball and Clarke goes forward and nudges it past Dhoni for four, it may have been a thick outside edge but Clarke intended to play it in that region
pushed to midwicket, Raina fires in the throw to the 'keepers end and concedes an overthrow
defended on the leg side
slips down leg side but the batsman had moved too far across for it to be called wide
outside off stump, the batsman tries to cut but misses
forced to deep midwicket for one
short of a length outside off stump, played past point
defended on the leg side
on off stump, no room on offer, driven to cover
played in front of midwicket for one
defended back to the bowler.
tossed up on off stump, Clarke leans forward and turns it to square leg
shorter this time, Clarke plays it to square leg again
shorter in length, Clarke goes down on one knee and paddles it wide of square leg for one
swept down to deep square leg
driven to long off for one
splendid catch! Tossed up on midle stump, Watson goes on the front foot and flicks it in the air towards midwicket where Raina dives forward to take a sharp low catch
defended back to the bowler
played back to Sehwag
on middle stump, Clarke uses his feet to step down and work it down the ground for one&
defended on the off side
pushed to midwicket
wide outside off stump but Cosgrove plays it straight to cover
drifts down leg side and clips the pad for a leg bye to short fine leg
tossed up, pitches outside off stump and angles away from Cosgrove who lets it go
worked behind square for one
that was much quicker from Harbhajan, Clarke pushes forward and the ball beats the outside edge
worked between square leg and midwicket for one
good length on off stump, Cosgrove plays back and defends on the off side
driven back to Sehwag on the front foot
worked in front of square and the batsmen thought about the single but Yuvraj dives across and cuts it off
played to point for one
quicker ball outside off stump, Cosgrove uses the pace and runs it past short third man
worked towards square leg for a single
pushed to midwicket on the back foot
tossed up on middle and off stump, Clarke plays it to wide mid-on but Raina dives across from short midwicket and cuts off the single
this time he plays it in front of midwicket for a single
out! caught at slip! Cosgrove pushes tentatively forward at one that spins away from him and gets the edge, Dravid takes a low catch at first slip
played to midwicket
pitches outside off and spins back into Haddin who plays back and defends
defended on the off side
short and on leg stump, Clarke pulls it to deep backward suare leg for one
defended to midwicket
pushed down to long-on for one
turned off the pads to short fine leg
Sehwag ends the over sloppily, the ball was driven back to him and a misfield allows the batsman two runs when there should have been none
tossed up on off stump, Clarke uses his feet to get forward and defends
defended to midwicket on the front foot
just wide of Raina at midwicket, Clarke was early on the shot and lobbed it tamely  towards midwicket
defended on the leg side
short outside off stump, cut to deep cover for one
defended on the leg side
cut off the back foot to deep point for one
shorter in length and Haddin steps forward and plays it to midwicket
played past cover for two runs, why is Munaf Patel at cover?
played back to the bowler
inside out and down to the wide long-off fence for four, there was no protection in the deep and the batsman did superbly to find the gap
pulled to deep square leg for a quick two runs
defended on the leg side
turned in front of square leg for a quick single
flatter ball on off stump, defended on the back foot on the leg side
drifting down leg side, wide called
played off the back foot but straight to point
defended on the back foot on the leg side
drifting down leg side, the ball clips the pads and runs down to fine leg, the batsmen call for three but settle for two
defended back to the bowler
driven down to long-on for one
tossed up and Haddin steps down and lofts it one bounce to long on
the batsman steps down, the ball hits the pad and runs down to third man for one, Sehwag appeals for what its worth and it's not worth much
played down to fine leg
defended on the front foot on the off side
defended back to Harbhajan
driven down to wide long- on for one
on middle stump, pushed straight to midwicket
defended to midwicket
outside off stump and Haddin tries to run it down to third man but gets beaten
flat and straight, Clarke plays it back to Sehwag
drifts down leg side, Clarke steps forward and tries to play it on the leg side, he gets a faint edge and the ball beats Dhoni and runs down to fine leg
defended on the leg side
defended back to the bowler
Haddin heaves it down the ground, doesn't time it well rnough and long-on runs around to field it
defended on the leg side
played off the back foot on the off side
pushed towards cover on the front foot
shorter in length and the batsmen run a sharp single to square leg
defended to midwicket
turned past square for one
defended back to the bowler
defended to midwicket
punched off the back foot to long off
pushed to long-on for one to bring up the 200

run-out! Quick thinking from Sehwag. Clarke drove it straight back to him and Haddin was backing up too far, Sehwag fielded the ball and flicked it back on to the stumps and Haddin was short of his crease
driven to long-on for one
played to mid-on
edged and Dhoni misses it, on off stump and Clarke pushes at it, the ball takes a faint edge and goes just wide of Dhoni
that cut back viciously into Clarke, it pitched just outside off and Clarke drove at it, the ball beats the inside edge
short of a length outside off stump, Hogg drives off the back foot to sweeper
pitches on leg stump and angles across Hogg who plays it to short third man
short in length and Hogg goes back and cuts it in front of point for one
tossed up on of and middle, Clarke steps down and drives it to long-on for one to move to 49
pushed to cover for a quick single
on off stump, Clarke gets forward and tries to drive but manages only a thick outside edge past cover for one. That's his fifty, well played
short, far too short. Clarke latches on it it very early and pulls it in front of midwicket for six
left alone outside off stump
on off stump, Clarke plays it with soft hands towards cover for a sharp single
on middle and off stump, worked off the bak foot to midwicket for one
miscued shot and it falls safe! It was full outside  off stump and Clarke tried to heave it out of the ground but gets a thick outside edge over cover, luckily for him it falls in no man's land
nearly in the blockhole this time, Clarke digs it out on the leg side
short in length outside off stump and Haddin cuts hard but straight to point
defended on the off side
angling into off stump from round the wicket, defended back to the bowler
pushed on the off side for one
quicker ball and shorter in length, the batsman swings it past short fine leg
short again and the batsman works it past fine leg again
tight line on off stump, defended back to the bowler
full on middle stump and the batsman worls it past  mid-on for one
short ball and Hogg tries to pull but doesn't make proper contact, the batsmen run one
played to deep midwicket for one
picthes on off stump and shapes away from the left-hander, Hogg tries to run it down to third man but misses
the batsman tries to play it on the leg side but the ball clips the pad through to Dhoni
and as I say that, Clarke lofts a full delivery down the ground, he didn't time that well enough and Raina at long-off takes a simple catch

short of a length on off stump and moves away a touch, the batsman wafts at it and gets a definite edge through to Dhoni. The Indians can't believe that wasn't given, perhaps it's all the darkness and thunder
played back to the bowler
played to cover for a sharp single
another one goes down, that pitches on off stump, bounces a touch extra and moves away from Johnson who tries to run it down to third man but gets an edge through to Dhoni.
cut off the back foot to deep point for one
short of a length outside off stump, driven off the back foot through covers
attempted yorker but a touch down leg side, clips the bat and pad
short of a length on off stump, driven down the ground on the back foot
short outside of stump and the batsman cuts towards point where Yuvraj Singh stood like a statue as the ball went past him for four. I don't think he spotted the ball coming his way
short of a length, the batsman goes back and drops the ball at his toes and sets off for a quick run
full and nearly in the blockhole, dug out down the ground for one
picthes outside off stump, bounces steply and moves away from Hogg who pokes at it and gets beaten
short of a length again and Hogg backs away to make room, the ball follows him and goes between the batsman and the stumps. Dhoni doesn't collect it cleanly
Munaf picks up his third. Clark backs away to make room again and flat bats it down the ground straight down long-off's throat
left alone outside off stump
short of a length on off stump, dabbed on the outside for a sharp single. Had there been a direct hit at the non-strikers end it could have been the end of the innings
that's the end of the innings. Full ball and Hogg throws his bat at it and skies it high in the air, Dhoni runs around and takes a well-judged catch

inn2.comm: pitches wide outside off stump and Dravid shoulders arms
pitches outside off stump and moves away from Dravid who lets it go
pitches outside off stump and cuts back into Dravid this time, he lets it go again
straighter line and on off stump, Dravid defends on the leg side
short of a length and in the channel outside off stump, Dravid puts a foot forward and shoulders arms
defended off the back foot on the off side
full on middle and leg and Tendulkar gets squared up and a thick edge runs down to third man
short of a length on middle stump, cuts back sharply into Dravid and hits him high on the pad
close to 85 mph, defended on the back foot back to the bowler
full and drifting down leg side, that clipped and Haddin collects well down leg side
on the pads again, clipped to square leg
straight ball, pushed back to the bowler

bang on the helmet, McGrath digs it in short and the ball doesn't get up as much as Tendulkar thought it would. He ducks into it and the ball crashes into the helmet. What a start to the McGrath-Tendulkar battle
beaten by a unplayable ball. That pitched on middle, opened up Tendulkar, and moved a touch away to beat the outside edge
worked through midwicket for a single
McGrath oversteps, that pitched outside off and moved away from Dravid who lets it go
good length on off stump, Dravid gets forward and plays it back to the bowler
wide outside off stump and moves wider after pitching.
left alone outside the off stump
this time it's the offcutter and it threads the gap between Dravid's bat and body.
short in length and the ball hits Tendulkar's thigh and the batsmen run one. However, the umpire rules it a dead ball
pitches on middle and off and Tendulkar offers no shot, the ball hits him on the pad outside the line of off stump, Australians go up in muted appeal
short ball, too short and the umpire calls it wide for height
drifts down leg side and that's easy for Tendulkar, he clips it down to fine leg for four
full and angles into middle and leg stump after pitching outside leg stump, hits Tendulkar on the pads
better line this time, pitching on off and moving away from Tendulkar who lets it go
full and in the blockhole just outside off stump, Tendulkar digs it out and back to the bowler
on off stump and just short of a length, dabbed on the off side for one
pitches just outside off stump and Tendulkar shoulders arms again but the ball cuts back in and hits him high on the pad. He didn't pick that offcutter
hit on the pad again, just short of a length and Tendulkar gets half forward and pushes at it
outside off stump and played with an open face down to third man
short in length and that one doesn't rise at all, Dravid swivels and pulls it to deep backward square leg for one
Tendulkar says enough is enough, he gives McGrath the charge and pulls him over midwicket and the ball reaches the fence even though it wasn't timed perfectly
full on middle and leg stump, driven to mid-on
short of a length, pitches outside off stump and move away from Dravid who fends at it but gets beaten
short ball and it doesn't rise that much, Dravid swivels and pulls it behind square to the fence
short of a length again outside the off stump, Dravid reaches out at it but the away movement beats the bat
the first wicket falls, short of a length and wide outside off stump, Dravid tries to loft over cover but doesn't get the elevation and offers a simple catch.
bowled first ball! short of a length, pitches on middle and off and moves away a touch, Pathan plays inside the line and the ball crashes into off stump
five wides ! banged in short and that bounces high and beats the keeper
cut to point on the front foot
upper cut for six! Short outside off stump, Sehwag gets under it and cuts it over third man
short of a length and in the channel outside off stump, Sehwag pokes forward and gets beaten

a disastrous mix up and Sehwag is run-out. He creamed that through covers but the ball pulled up in the soggy outfield. The batsmen ran two and Sehwag went for the third. Tendulkar initially set off but then decided against it. However, Sehwag kept coming and was left stranded mid-pitch when the throw came in from the deep to the wicketkeeper
played with an open face to point
and Tendulkar goes as well! Full and outside off stump, Tendulkar goes for the drive and gets a thickish outside edge, Haddin takes it easily
straight ball, Raina pushes forward and gets an edge past square leg for one
short of a length on off stump, defended off the back foot
short off a length just outside off stump, punched off the back foot to cover
Johnson is on fire! Short on a length on off stump, moves a shade away, Yuvraj fends aimlessly outside off stump, gets an edge and first slip gleefully accepts the offering
